Adding locally hosted code (Local Repository) to GitHub

  This can be done in 2 ways:
  > GitHub CLI
  > GitHub Desktop


GitHub CLI:
1) Initialize the Git repository
2) Importing a Git repository

  > Initializing a Git repository
    > using Git 2.28.0 or a later version
      > git init -b main
    > using Git 2.27.1 or an earlier version (Name of the default branch can be set using git symbolic-ref)
      > git init && git symbolic-ref HEAD refs/heads/main 
    > git add .
    > git commit -m "First commit"


REF: https://docs.github.com/en/migrations/importing-source-code/using-the-command-line-to-import-source-code/adding-locally-hosted-code-to-github#adding-a-local-repository-to-github-using-git

